            Gal Barby
          
          
            
              I am a statistics-economics student at the University
              of Haifa, interested in data and teaching. I serve as an
              assistant lecturer in Econometrics and Microeconomics
              courses.
              My hobbies include sports, chess and playing guitar. I
              compete in powerlifting competitions and also prepare
              athletes for powerlifting competitions.
